  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Community Resilience to Recurrent Floods in the Terai Region of Nepal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reduce the vulnerability of poor and marginalized communities (including dalits) in flood prone districts of the Terai Region of Nepal. The project shall be implemented in the 28 communities of Saptari, Sarlahi and Nawalparasi districts at local level while there will be national level advocacy, coordination and networking. The project shall directly benefit 21,407 people from community, schools, government and non -government actors in disaster risk reduction. This project, with learning from previous DIPECHO/regular DRR projects, focuses on local disaster management components, IEC, small -scale mitigation and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
